OL,3,CPost Office Inquiry: Horizon scandal
OL,4,Cdrove 13 people to suicide, report
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FIt emphasised the human cost of the
OL,8,Fscandal and criticised the failure to
OL,9,Fprovide adequate redress, following
OL,10,Fyears of ambiguous and inconsistent
OL,11,Ffinancial compensation offers from the
OL,12,FPost Office.
OL,14,FThe inquiry estimates that as many as
OL,15,F10,000 people may have been affected
OL,16,Fby the Horizon scandal, including both
OL,17,Fconvicted subpostmasters and those who
OL,18,Fexperienced financial or reputational
OL,19,Fdamage as a result of the system's
OL,20,Ffailures.
